==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suet
<hw>Su"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>suet</ets>,
dim. fr. OF. <ets>seu</ets>, <ets>suif</ets>, F. <ets>suif</ets>, L.
<ets>sebum</ets>. Cf. <er>Soap</er>, <er>Sebaceous</er>.]</ety> <def>The
fat and fatty tissues of an animal, especially the harder fat about the
kidneys and loins in beef and mutton, which, when melted and freed from
the membranes, forms tallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

